{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":65270,"duration_api_ms":65246,"num_turns":3,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"a8dd80d3-1b1c-450b-a748-501a0a86f65e","total_cost_usd":0.2607633,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24272,"cache_read_input_tokens":78002,"output_tokens":1556,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":24272,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":1556,"cacheReadInputTokens":78002,"cacheCreationInputTokens":24272,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.22962100000000002,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":10,"outputTokens":3656,"cacheReadInputTokens":25948,"cacheCreationInputTokens":8206,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.0311423,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Reviewed four amendments concerning failure classification and retry semantics in the process backend adapter. Three amendments identify genuine bugs or coverage gaps that should be addressed: a missing test for the spawn-failure BinaryNotFound path, a semantic mismatch where timeouts produce InvocationFailed instead of InvocationTimeout (breaking worktree timeout recovery), and BackendUnavailable deterministic failures being wastefully retried 5 times. The fourth amendment proposes reclassifying post-spawn exit codes, which conflicts with the deliberate two-layer design where spawn-time detection handles missing binaries and post-spawn exit codes are treated as application-defined.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-4-436d5926","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified the code: process_backend.rs maps ErrorKind::NotFound at spawn() to FailureClass::BinaryNotFound, and retry_policy.rs makes BinaryNotFound terminal (0 retries). However, no existing test exercises invoke() with a truly missing binary to confirm this spawn-failure path. The exit-code-127 test (lines 2038-2066) only tests post-spawn classification, and check_availability tests cover a different code path. If someone accidentally broke the ErrorKind::NotFound → BinaryNotFound mapping, missing binaries could fall through to TransportFailure and burn 5 retry attempts. This is a critical non-retryable path that deserves a direct regression test."},{"amendment_id":"fr-4-edade531","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed the bug by reading the code. The timeout handler at process_backend.rs:1044 calls Self::invocation_failed() which creates AppError::InvocationFailed { failure_class: Timeout }, not AppError::InvocationTimeout. The service's map_invoke_error (service.rs:369-378) passes InvocationFailed through unchanged. Meanwhile, worktree.rs:894 specifically pattern-matches on AppError::InvocationTimeout { .. } to trigger timeout-specific recovery (aborting a rebase and classifying as RebaseFailureClassification::Timeout). Since the adapter produces InvocationFailed rather than InvocationTimeout, the worktree timeout handler will never fire for adapter-enforced timeouts — the error will fall through to the generic Unknown classification branch. This is a real semantic mismatch that breaks timeout-specific recovery logic."},{"amendment_id":"fr-4-5affc00d","decision":"accept","rationale":"Confirmed by reading error.rs:306: AppError::BackendUnavailable maps to FailureClass::TransportFailure, which gets 5 retries with backoff per retry_policy.rs:47. check_availability() (process_backend.rs:1171-1193) correctly identifies deterministic fatal conditions — missing binaries and unset OPENROUTER_API_KEY — as BackendUnavailable. These conditions cannot self-resolve between retry attempts: a missing binary won't appear, and an unset env var won't become set. With the 5-retry transport budget, these fatal setup problems will burn 5 futile attempts plus exponential backoff before failing. BackendUnavailable should map to a terminal failure class to fail immediately on these unrecoverable configuration issues."},{"amendment_id":"fr-4-34a6baf2","decision":"reject","rationale":"The current behavior is a deliberate, well-documented design choice. The comment at process_backend.rs:1442-1450 explicitly explains: once a process is running, any exit code (including 127) is application-defined and should not be treated as a missing-binary signal. This is architecturally sound — exit codes are ambiguous after successful spawn. A wrapper CLI might exit 127 for application-specific reasons unrelated to a missing subordinate binary. The system already has the correct two-layer approach: check_availability() for pre-invocation validation and ErrorKind::NotFound at spawn() for binary-missing detection. The concern about interpreter-missing scenarios burning 5 retries is better addressed by amendments fr-4-5affc00d (making BackendUnavailable terminal) and fr-4-436d5926 (testing spawn-time BinaryNotFound), not by trying to reinterpret ambiguous post-spawn exit codes."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"dfae78ae-2cc3-4d2f-a0c9-f04557b94eb7"}
